  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Ok so the issue here is that the currentRefinedValues is not reading generic searchParameters, only refinements: https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blame/e81c320a0f025332c9fdbb4bb0177eada54216cd/src/lib/utils.js#L159\n\ngeoloc is only a searchParameter, what we could do is that if we find a match for the name of the attribute inside the searchParameters then we accept it. So that you do not have to declare a fake facet.\n",
    "created_at": "2016-05-25T16:24:53Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1002#issuecomment-221629840",
    "id": 221629840,
